Philippines Stocks: Philex Mining, RFM Corp., Swift Foods

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-28T04:10:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/alliance-cebu-philex-san-miguel-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index was little changed at
4,482.80.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s largest metals
producer, climbed for a third day, increasing 2 percent to 25.50
pesos as earnings rose. It’s the stock’s longest rally since
July 4. The company reported first-half net income of 3.22
billion pesos ($76 million), compared with 965 million pesos a
year ago, a stock-exchange filing showed.  Swift Foods Inc. (SFI)  , a poultry raiser that posted
losses in the previous three years, sank 2.5 percent to 19.4
centavos after parent  RFM Corp. (RFM)   said it will pay 70.54
million convertible preferred Swift shares as a property
dividend. RFM decreased 0.8 percent to 1.31 pesos, the lowest
close this week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
